    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="154"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d154">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_CC2" type="from"
                            >Churchill</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_RFD1" type="to"
                            >Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d154fn1">Sent to London; forwarded by the American Embassy,
                        London, apparently via military channels and the White House Map Room, to
                            <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> in North Africa,
                        Regarding <persName corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName>’s concern after
                        this message had been sent, lest it give offense, see <persName
                            corresp="#p_CC2">Churchill</persName>, p. 327.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Cairo</hi>
                        </placeName>?] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-21">21 November
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Unnumbered (#507)<note n="2" xml:id="d154fn2">The parenthetical information is
                        handwritten on the source text.</note>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval Person</gloss> to President
                        <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> most immediate personal and
                    most secret.</p>
                <p>See St. <persName>John</persName>, chapter 14, verses 1 to 4.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d154fn3">
                        <p>The source text contains, at the bottom of the page, the verses cited, as
                            follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <list>
                                    <item>“1. Let not your heart be troubled: ye believe in God,
                                        believe also in me.</item>
                                    <item>“2. In my Father’s house are many mansions; if it were not
                                        so, I would have told you, I go to prepare a place for
                                        you.</item>
                                    <item>“3. And if I go and prepare a place for you, I will come
                                        again, and receive you unto myself; that where I am, there
                                        ye may be also.</item>
                                    <item>“4. And whither I go ye know, and the way ye know.”</item>
                                </list>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                    </note>
                </p>
            </div>
        </body>
